<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_6d2f5ed0-c822-48b0-ac7a-bcdda0a91f0d" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>J6D13</sptc><title id="_5d7a4a70-9cfe-4dcf-8b05-81d0a42a9126">Heat rejection equipment</title><archive-num/><subclause id="_e180573e-03d1-4915-9314-6e6fd87721a7" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_fd9bc5cf-e6e5-4a9c-8476-7225f680c2c1">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The motor rated power of a fan in a cooling tower, closed circuit cooler or evaporative condenser must not exceed the allowances in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/114_0.9.0.xml#_c6671383-77d4-45d2-9708-c7180fd3256a" id="_c52b8f7e-228c-4180-b3d5-e0405f62bc51" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table J6D13</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_f662d744-8f78-469a-8ee0-30b811eb5bed" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_843a2594-a130-4142-a209-c6fe7b076e65">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The fan in an air-cooled condenser must have a motor rated power of not more than 42 W for each kW of heat rejected from the refrigerant when determined in accordance with AHRI 460.</p></subclause><subclause id="_7b53a9ce-1532-4f03-a9e8-28ccf8372547" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_f7026e12-ff3a-4cae-ac9d-69f84ccf2414">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>A fan with a three-phase motor in heat rejection equipment must be capable of variable speed operation.</p></subclause><subclause id="_e9ff082e-e600-4e91-8091-9433eec36e7a" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_0f034454-371c-47a7-9056-8b576ad29621">SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>The requirements of (2) and (3) do not apply to—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_86ce9d8f-48da-4d05-88ef-823b057ae58b">a fan in a refrigerant chiller of an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1181_1.0.0.xml#_386d327a-f182-4f1a-bf21-5cfdef50cc8d" id="_fdea7400-147b-4986-86a2-2e52d880b53f" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">air-conditioning</xref> system that complies with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/3449_3.25.0.xml#_94a83bdf-f1ff-40fa-a05d-45c68d4cd1bd" id="_93443ab1-8c4e-406e-ad2a-237e5425e4d2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">J6D11</xref>; and</li><li id="_511aa106-6f8c-431c-b351-1f255c5bf9c1">fans in unitary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1181_1.0.0.xml#_386d327a-f182-4f1a-bf21-5cfdef50cc8d" id="_19ca7b89-8419-4ade-a159-a117432df641" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">air-conditioning</xref> equipment, such as a packaged air-conditioners, a split system or a variable refrigerant flow unit that complies with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/3450_3.29.0.xml#_640423c8-66a7-45e4-a9ba-0c927e7ef28c" id="_8d5e46be-0f86-4ba1-b563-840ac6969f66" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">J6D12</xref>; and</li><li id="_45dbf2b4-ecdf-4275-a037-eb6b5ceda977">a fan in a 4-pipe chiller or air source heat pump water heater that complies with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/3446_3.34.0.xml#_7b273421-c4c5-444a-b7e1-e3f635bd3c20" id="_700779ee-845b-460d-a965-8840ca8ba86b" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">J6D10</xref>(8).</li></ol></subclause><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/114_0.9.0.xml" graph="None" id="_c6671383-77d4-45d2-9708-c7180fd3256a"><num/><title id="_2836ed0d-1ccc-4c94-8ded-e3fa666917f7"/></table-reference></clause>